    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-01-15T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-01-15T18:00:00-05:00" n="449"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d449">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 656.119/133a</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_PWH1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Page</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-01-15T18:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 15, 1918, 6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>6252. For <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SLP1">Sheldon</persName> from
                    War Trade Board:</p>
                <p>Your No. 21, 12th. We agree to Dutch proposal with following slight changes: Of
                    the 150,000 tons, part to be employed in Belgian Relief, part to be used for
                    supplying Switzerland, which is cargo <pb facs="0556" n="1390" xml:id="pg_1390"
                    /> under safe conduct, remaining tonnage to be used in trades outside Europe and
                    Atlantic islands. We are willing to allow the <hi rend="italic">Samarinda</hi>
                    and <hi rend="italic">Adonis</hi> to go forward, or <hi rend="italic"
                        >Zeelandia</hi> in substitution for either one of them, upon understanding
                    that equivalent amount of tonnage will be dispatched from Holland at same time.
                    Sorry cannot agree to release of four remaining vessels mentioned your cable.
                    The two vessels coming from Holland must be assigned to trades outside Europe
                    and Atlantic islands, the same as tonnage first above mentioned. Hope you will
                    obtain two round trips instead of one if operated in short voyage trade, but we
                    are not insisting upon this now. Telegraph immediately in order to get the
                    matter concluded.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
